--> Make income statement first, from the expenses and income

net profit = income - expenses

--> income statement doesnt depend on other statements

Make Balance sheet 

Retained earnings from income statement goes to balance steet, equity section

assets = liabilities + equity

--> make cash flow statement

net cash flow = cash inflows - cash outflows  --> Direct method (actual cash receipts or payments)

Indirect method: adjust net profit by adding non cash expenses , changes in working capital , financing

Direct method: find the net cash flow using the receipts